## Stream 1: Core Function Hardening

### Objective
Close all remaining edge cases, performance issues, and UX gaps in Organizations, Opportunities, Orders, and core workflows.

### Deliverables

#### A) Organizations Module Hardening
- Bulk account import/export functionality
- Account merge and deduplication workflows
- Athlete director / head coach / admin role separation with permissions
- Contact information validation (phone, email placeholder detection)
- Account status lifecycle (active, inactive, archived)
- **Tests:** Unit, integration, and E2E coverage for all workflows
- **Performance:** P95 latency <500ms for list/detail queries

#### B) Opportunities Module Hardening
- Stage transition guardrails (prevent invalid transitions)
- Required field enforcement per stage (e.g., mockup specs, invoice amount)
- Bulk opportunity updates and status changes
- Duplicate opportunity detection
- Lane/product/sport classification consistency
- **Tests:** Full E2E for lead-to-close journey with all stage transitions
- **Performance:** Pipeline query <1s for 1000+ opportunities

#### C) Order Management & Invoicing
- Order creation from opportunity (auto-populate fields)
- Invoice PDF generation and delivery (via queue, not blocking UI)
- Payment reconciliation and status tracking
- Handoff confirmation workflow (design complete? payment received?)
- **Tests:** End-to-end order-to-payment journey
- **SLO:** Invoice delivery <5 minutes from creation

#### D) API Reliability & Error Handling
- All endpoints return structured error responses (error code, message, retry hint)
- Rate limiting and quota enforcement
- Request deduplication for idempotent operations
- Circuit breaker for external service calls (email, PDF generation)
- **Tests:** Chaos engineering scenarios (service down, slow response, timeouts)

#### E) Frontend UX Polish
- Loading states and skeleton screens on all pages
- Real-time validation and form error feedback
- Undo/redo for critical operations (stage advance, bulk updates)
- Search/filter performance on large datasets (debouncing, pagination)
- Responsive design for mobile (reps in field use phones)
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for screen readers, keyboard navigation

### Exit Gates

- ✅ All critical user journeys (lead creation → close → invoice) tested E2E
- ✅ P95 latency benchmarks met for all major queries
- ✅ Zero data loss scenarios (rollback drills, backup restoration)
- ✅ Security scan passes (no SQL injection, XSS, CSRF vulnerabilities)
- ✅ Staging environment mirrors production; smoke tests pass
- ✅ Runbooks complete for ops team (deploy, rollback, incident response)

