## Stream 2: Notes & Activities (Unified Interaction Timeline)

### Objective
Enable reps to document interactions (calls, emails, meetings, notes) and give leadership visibility into deal progress, rep performance, and coaching opportunities.

**Business Value:** Regional director feedback — this is a **rep enablement + leadership tool** for account continuity and sales development.

### Deliverables

#### A) Activity Logging Modal & UI

**Frontend Component:**
- Modal triggered from Organization and Opportunity detail pages ("Log Activity" button)
- Activity type selector (Call, Email, Meeting, Note, Task)
- Rich text editor for notes (basic formatting: bold, italic, lists)
- Optional fields:
  - Due date (for tasks → reminder system in v2.1)
  - Participant names
  - Outcome/next steps
- Auto-capture: current user, timestamp, entity (org/opp)
- Submit → activity saved and timeline refreshed

**Timeline Display:**
- Chronological list (newest first) of all activities
- Activity type badge with icon (☎️ Call, ✉️ Email, 💬 Note, etc.)
- Rep name and timestamp
- Note preview (first 100 chars, expand on click)
- Immutable — no edit/delete (audit trail protection)

#### B) Backend API & Data Model

**Endpoints:**
- `POST /activities` — Create activity (call, email, note, task)
- `GET /organizations/:id/activities` — List org activities
- `GET /opportunities/:id/activities` — List opp activities
- `GET /activities/:id` — View single activity detail

**Data Model:**
```
Activity {
  id: UUID
  type: 'CALL' | 'EMAIL' | 'MEETING' | 'NOTE' | 'TASK'
  entityType: 'ORGANIZATION' | 'OPPORTUNITY'
  entityId: UUID
  content: string (rich text)
  createdBy: UUID (user who logged)
  createdAt: timestamp
  dueDate?: timestamp (for tasks)
  participants?: string[]
  tags?: string[] (for filtering/search)
  
  — immutable; no update/delete allowed
}
```

**Constraints:**
- Activities are immutable (audit trail = no modifications)
- Authorized users only (must have access to org/opp)
- Server-side validation (no XSS in notes)
- Indexing on entityId + createdAt for fast timeline queries

#### C) Integration with Existing Entities

- Activity timeline appears on Organization detail page
- Activity timeline appears on Opportunity detail page
- Activities tied to org and opp separately (both visible on parent org)
- Add activity from either org or opp page (context-aware)

#### D) Search & Filtering (Phase 1 MVP)

- Filter activities by type (show only calls, notes, etc.)
- Date range filter (activities from last 30 days, etc.)
- Full-text search on note content
- **Future (v2.1):** AI-powered insights ("common objections", "decision timeline")

### Exit Gates

- ✅ Modal opens, logs activity, timeline refreshes immediately
- ✅ All activity types (call, email, meeting, note, task) work end-to-end
- ✅ Activities immutable (no edit/delete via UI or API)
- ✅ Timeline queries <500ms (even with 1000+ activities)
- ✅ Permissions enforced (reps can't see activities on accounts they don't own)
- ✅ E2E test: create activity → verify audit trail → attempt (fail) to delete
- ✅ Regional director approves UX and workflow
- ✅ All activities logged for ops visibility (who logged what, when)

