## Stream 3: TUF Academy Core (Onboarding & Certification Framework)

### Objective
Build the backbone for coaching, enablement, and rep certification. Reps complete onboarding, study curriculum, and earn certifications (Athlete Management, Sales Process, Product Knowledge).

**Business Value:** Ensure all reps are trained on playbook, reduce onboarding time, create certification path for career development.

### Deliverables

#### A) Academy Dashboard & Navigation
- Hero section: rep's current progress (onboarding %, certifications earned)
- "Your Learning Path" — modules assigned by role (new rep vs. veteran vs. manager)
- "Available Certifications" — browse all cert tracks
- "Completed & In Progress" — progress bar and completion date
- Rep profile: certifications earned, completion dates, renewal dates (if applicable)

#### B) Onboarding Module (Mandatory for All Reps)
- 5-10 core lessons covering:
  - TUF brand/values/products
  - Sales process (lead sourcing → close → handoff)
  - CRM navigation (this app: organizations, opportunities, orders)
  - Playbook essentials (objection handling, discovery questions)
  - Compliance (data privacy, contract signing, approval workflows)
- Lesson format:
  - Short video (2-5 min) or text + images
  - Checkpoint quiz (80% pass required to unlock next lesson)
  - Progress saved locally; completion marked in LMS
- **Completion gate:** Onboarding MUST be done before rep can log in to sales app (first-time setup)

#### C) Certification Tracks (Launch with 3)
1. **Athlete Management** — Understanding athlete decision-making, building relationships, follow-up cadence
2. **Sales Process Excellence** — Qualification, discovery, proposal, negotiation, close
3. **Product Knowledge** — All TUF product lines, customization options, pricing, inventory

Each track:
- 3-5 lessons (videos, articles, scenarios)
- 1 quiz per lesson (pass/fail)
- Final capstone quiz or scenario-based assessment (>75% to pass)
- Completion certificate (downloadable, social shareable)
- Expiration date optional (e.g., annual renewal for compliance)

#### D) Manager Workflows
- **Assign Certifications** — Manager can assign cert tracks to individual reps or teams
- **Track Progress** — Dashboard showing rep's module/cert completion % across team
- **Download Reports** — CSV export of team onboarding & cert status
- **Coaching Notes** — Attach feedback to rep's profile (visible to rep and manager)

#### E) Admin Controls
- Create/edit/delete modules, lessons, quizzes (WYSIWYG editor)
- Bulk upload lessons (markdown or structured JSON)
- A/B test lessons (track engagement, completion %)
- Audit trail: who created/updated content, when, by whom

### Exit Gates

- ✅ Onboarding can be completed end-to-end (lessons → quizzes → certificate)
- ✅ Three certification tracks available and testable
- ✅ Reps cannot access sales app without onboarding completion (permissions enforced)
- ✅ Manager dashboard shows team progress accurately
- ✅ Certificates downloadable and shareable
- ✅ All lesson content indexed and searchable
- ✅ E2E scenario: new rep → onboarding → cert → ready for production

